---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Remote Tech Support | Jake Fixes Tech — Littleton, NH"
description="Remote computer support via phone, video call or remote control. I can troubleshoot and fix many software issues without you leaving home. Windows, Mac, Linux and Chromebook.">

  <!-- Header Banner -->
  <section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;background-color:rgb(30,64,175);">
    <img src="/hero.jpg" alt="Professional tech workspace with dual monitors" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;z-index:0;" />
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(30,64,175,0.88),rgba(37,99,235,0.88));z-index:1;"></div>
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;position:relative;z-index:2;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#93c5fd;">
        <a href="/services#remote-support" style="color:#93c5fd;text-decoration:none;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Services</a>
      </p>
      <h1 style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:white;line-height:1.2;">Remote Support</h1>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;color:#bfdbfe;line-height:1.75;font-size:1.1rem;max-width:42rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        Can't make it in? No problem. I can diagnose and fix many software issues remotely by phone, video call, or by taking control of your screen directly. Windows, Mac, Linux and Chromebook all supported.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#1e40af;font-weight:700;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          Get Remote Help
          <svg style="height:1rem;width:1rem;" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/pricing" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          View Pricing
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Info Bar -->
  <section style="background:#1e40af;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:2rem;text-align:center;">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">$65/hr</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Remote Sessions</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">No Travel</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Help From Anywhere</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">All Platforms</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Win, Mac, Linux, Chrome</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">How It Works</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Three Ways to Get Remote Help</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">Depending on what you need, we can handle it by phone, over a video call, or I can take control of your screen directly and fix it myself. I'll recommend the right approach when you reach out.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.6 1.28h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.96a16 16 0 0 0 6.29 6.29l.54-.54a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 21.28 17z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Phone Call</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Best for quick questions, talking through a problem, or figuring out next steps together. Low barrier. No apps, no setup, just a call. A good starting point if you're not sure what kind of help you need.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #7c3aed;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#ede9fe;color:#6d28d9;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polygon points="23 7 16 12 23 17 23 7"/><rect x="1" y="5" width="15" height="14" rx="2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Video Call with Screen Share</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">You share your screen so I can see exactly what's happening while we talk through it together. Great for software troubleshooting, walking through settings, or tech tutoring sessions. Uses <strong>Google Meet</strong> or <strong>Zoom</strong>. I'll send you a link and no account is required on your end.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #15803d;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#dcfce7;color:#15803d;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Full Remote Control</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">I take control of your mouse and keyboard directly and fix the problem myself while you watch. The most hands-off option for you. Works on Windows, Mac, Linux and Chromebook via <strong>Chrome Remote Desktop</strong>. I'll walk you through the one-time setup, which takes about a minute.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Can Fix Remotely -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">What's Possible Remotely</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What I Can Help With</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">Most software problems can be handled without me ever needing to touch your device in person. Here are the most common remote requests.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(15rem,1fr));gap:1rem;">
        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Virus &amp; Malware Removal</h3>
          <p>Pop-ups, slow performance, strange behavior. I can run a full clean remotely on Windows, Mac or Linux without your computer leaving your desk.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Software Troubleshooting</h3>
          <p>Apps crashing, updates breaking things, programs that won't open. Diagnosed and fixed across all major operating systems.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>OS Setup &amp; Configuration</h3>
          <p>Fresh Windows or macOS install follow-up, settings configuration, user account setup, privacy settings and getting everything working the way you want.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 6 2 18 2 18 9"/><path d="M6 18H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h16a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v5a2 2 0 0 1-2 2h-2"/><rect x="6" y="14" width="12" height="8"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Printer &amp; Peripheral Issues</h3>
          <p>Driver problems, printers that won't connect, devices that aren't being recognized. Many printer issues are software-side and fully fixable remotely.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12.55a11 11 0 0 1 14.08 0"/><path d="M1.42 9a16 16 0 0 1 21.16 0"/><path d="M8.53 16.11a6 6 0 0 1 6.95 0"/><circle cx="12" cy="20" r="1" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Network &amp; WiFi Troubleshooting</h3>
          <p>Devices that won't stay connected, slow speeds, VPN issues and other network problems that can be diagnosed from your end without a visit.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Tech Tutoring &amp; Walkthroughs</h3>
          <p>Learning a new program, getting comfortable with your device, or just need someone to walk you through something step by step. See <a href="/services/tech-tutoring" style="color:#2563eb;font-weight:600;">Tech Tutoring</a> for more.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><circle cx="12" cy="16" r="1" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Second Opinion &amp; Advice</h3>
          <p>Not sure if a repair is worth doing? Wondering if you need a new computer? A quick call or video session can save you money and time before you make a decision.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Email &amp; Account Setup</h3>
          <p>Setting up email clients, recovering accounts, configuring two-factor authentication or just getting a new email account sorted out properly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Doesn't Work Remotely -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Honest Limitations</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What Remote Can't Fix</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">Remote support is great for software, but it has real limits. Here's when you'd need to come in or have me visit instead.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Hardware Repairs</h3>
            <p>Broken screens, failing drives, RAM upgrades and any physical repair need hands on the device. Those require a drop-off or an <a href="/services/on-site-tech-support" style="color:#2563eb;font-weight:600;">on-site visit</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Device Won't Power On</h3>
            <p>If the computer won't boot at all, there's nothing to remote into. That needs to come in for diagnosis in person.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12.55a11 11 0 0 1 14.08 0"/><path d="M1.42 9a16 16 0 0 1 21.16 0"/><path d="M8.53 16.11a6 6 0 0 1 6.95 0"/><circle cx="12" cy="20" r="1" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>No Internet Connection</h3>
            <p>Remote support requires an active internet connection. If your connection is completely down, an on-site visit or drop-off is the way to go.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Platforms -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Tools I Use</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Platforms &amp; Compatibility</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">I'll always tell you which tool to use and walk you through the setup. It's usually just a single click or a short link.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;gap:1rem;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
        <div class="platform-card" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
            <div style="display:flex;height:2.5rem;width:2.5rem;min-width:2.5rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin:0;">Chrome Remote Desktop</h3>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#6b7280;line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Full remote control on Windows, Mac, Linux and Chromebook. Requires Google Chrome, which most people already have. If not, it's a free install. I'll send you a simple link and walk you through the one-time setup, which takes about a minute.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="platform-card">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
            <div style="display:flex;height:2.5rem;width:2.5rem;min-width:2.5rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polygon points="23 7 16 12 23 17 23 7"/><rect x="1" y="5" width="15" height="14" rx="2"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin:0;">Zoom</h3>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#6b7280;line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Video calls with screen share and remote control on Windows and Mac. Good for sessions where we need to talk through things together while I work. No account needed to join a call.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="platform-card">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
            <div style="display:flex;height:2.5rem;width:2.5rem;min-width:2.5rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M15 10l4.553-2.069A1 1 0 0 1 21 8.87v6.26a1 1 0 0 1-1.447.894L15 14"/><rect x="1" y="6" width="14" height="12" rx="2"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin:0;">Google Meet</h3>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#6b7280;line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Lightweight video calls with screen sharing. Works in any browser, no app needed, and I just send you a link. Great for tutoring sessions or when we only need to see your screen.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e40af,#2563eb);padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;">
    <div style="max-width:40rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin-bottom:1rem;">Need Help Right Now?</h2>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:1.1rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:2rem;">Reach out and describe what's going on. I'll let you know if remote support can handle it and get you sorted quickly.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#2563eb;font-weight:700;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          Get in Touch
        </a>
        <a href="tel:+18022341552" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.6 1.28h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.96a16 16 0 0 0 6.29 6.29l.54-.54a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 21.28 17z"/></svg>
          (802) 234-1552
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:0.875rem;margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <a href="/services#remote-support" style="color:#bfdbfe;text-decoration:underline;" aria-label="Back to all services">Back to All Services</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .service-item { background: white; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1.25rem; }
  .service-icon { height: 3rem; width: 3rem; min-width: 3rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .service-icon svg { height: 1.5rem; width: 1.5rem; }
  .item-title { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.375rem; }
  .item-desc { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .repair-card { background: #f8fafc; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem; }
  .repair-icon { display: flex; height: 2.5rem; width: 2.5rem; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-radius: 0.5rem; background: #dbeafe; color: #2563eb; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .repair-icon svg { height: 1.25rem; width: 1.25rem; }
  .repair-card h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.375rem; }
  .repair-card p { font-size: 0.875rem; color: #6b7280; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
  .platform-card { background: #f8fafc; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem; }
